Events

   Experience HRE Live
   [21]Past Events

February 2016

   February 23 ^rd

HRE Club Tour | Tesla

   HRE CLUB TOUR | TESLA will be a free, Tesla-focused evening with a
   presentation and factory tour from HRE President, Alan Peltier. Limited
   to 100 guests, this event will dive into the important aspects of wheel
   design and manufacturing geared toward Tesla vehicles. Hors d'oeuvres
   and beer/wine will be served. Bring your Tesla and your curiosity.


   [22]Details

March 2016

   March 12 ^th

HRE Experience Event | Corvette

   HRE Experience Event | Corvette will be a free, Corvette-focused event
   with presentations from the best automotive companies in the world.
   Limited to 100 guests, this event will dive into the important and
   exciting aspects of some of the key components of the Chevrolet
   Corvette. Each registrant will receive an HRE gift pack, catered lunch
   and one-on-one time with representatives from top companies. Bring your
   Corvette and your curiosity.
   [23]Details
   March 17 ^th

TX2k16

   This year, TX2k16 will be held at the Royal Purple Raceway and
   Ellington Airport in Houston, Tx.

   Drags, Roll Race, Dyno, Night Meet and more!
   [24]Details
   March 19 ^th

Targa Trophy 5th Annual German Car Festival

   Since 2007, Targa Trophy is about Southern California car culture and
   the active lifestyle. So Cal may be the only destination in the world
   that allows for so much active diversity – with the automobile and
   one’s personal aesthetic being two of the biggest key statements of
   style. It’s a one of a kind way of life and inspiration can be drawn
   everywhere you look. This is what motivates the world of Targa Trophy.
   Join us for the ride on March 19 as we call upon all German vehicles
   for the first Targa Trophy rally of the year, kicking off at HRE
   Performance Wheels at 8am.
   [25]Details

April 2016

   April 8 ^th

2016 California Festival of Speed

   The California Festival of Speed is the Porsche enthusiasts dream
   weekend. Club Race, Time Trial, Swap meet, Porsche Corral, Porsche For
   Sale Platz, Porsche Timeline Display, Vendor Row, Concours, Taste of
   Autocross, Parade Laps, Friends, Fun and all things Porsche. Need we
   say more? This event has race cars, show cars, it can even have your
   car! See the cars, meet the drivers and experience the excitement!
   [26]Details

June 2016

   June 4 ^th

2016 HRE Wheels Open House

   HRE Wheels opens up its doors for the annual HRE Open House featuring a
   massive gathering of supercars and sports cars from all over
   California, along with special guests including The Smoking Tire’s Matt
   Farah as the master of ceremonies, wheel and sponsor product giveaways
   and much more!

   Registration coming soon.
   [27]Details

August 2016

   August 19 ^th

2016 Werks Reunion

   The Porsche Club of America will hold it's second annual Werks Reunion
   Friday, August 14, 2015. It is the premier Porsche event and will take
   place during the world-famous "Monterey Car Week" on California's
   Monterey Peninsula. In years past, PCA co-hosted Legends of the
   Autobahn at the Rancho Canada Golf Club.

   Attendees will be treated to a stunning display of more than 500
   Porsches and vendor booths, and the camaraderie of fellow car
   enthusiasts. The 2015 show will feature the latest Porsches, special
   vehicle presentations, celebrity guests, and a surprise or two.
   [28]Details
   August 23 ^rd

Oktoberfest 2016

   Each year the BMW Car Club of America throws a party—a world famous
   party known as Oktoberfest and sometimes simply O'fest. This movable
   celebration of everything BMW occurs at exciting locations throughout
   the country and is the ultimate motorsport family reunion!

   O’Fest 2016 will be part of a once-in-a-lifetime celebration spanning
   almost two weeks in honor of BMW’s 100th anniversary. The event will be
   held in conjunction with two other favorite club events—Legends of the
   Autobahn and the Festorics Turn Five corral—so you do not want to miss
   this historic event. The host hotel for O’fest will be the Hyatt
   Monterey and the track is, of course, the thrilling Laguna Seca
   Raceway. Yes, finally you, too, will drive the Corkscrew!
   [29]Details

November 2016

   November 1 ^st

2016 SEMA Show

   The SEMA Show is the premier automotive specialty products trade event
   in the world. It draws the industry’s brightest minds and hottest
   products to one place, the Las Vegas Convention Center. In addition,
   the SEMA Show provides attendees with educational seminars, product
   demonstrations, special events, networking opportunities and more.
   [30]Details

December 2016

   December 3 ^rd

Motor4Toys

   Motor4Toys held it's 12th Annual charity car show last year, raising
   60,000 toys for children in need. The Auto Gallery, HRE Wheels and many
   more sponsors were on site to support the event with the rest of the
   car community. For 2016, we're gearing up for an even bigger #M4T!

   Founded by Dustin Troyan, Motor4Toys is a non-profit foundation that
   supports children in need and collects toy donations all year long
   leading up to Motor4Toys - this year the event expects 5,000 cars.
   Entrance to the event is FREE for everyone. We ask that each guest
   bring along at least one new, unwrapped toy, valued at over $10. Come
   and join us for a beautiful, sunnny day with the most spectacular high
   end automobiles the world has to offer...and all for a great cause!
   [31]Details
